SIMPLE: timeless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Timeless
<hw>Time"less</hw> <pr>(t⟦imac⟧m"l⟦ecr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Done at an improper time; unseasonable; untimely.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor fits it to prolong the heavenly feast⟦br⟧
<qex>Timeless</qex>, indecent.</q> <rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Done or occurring before the proper time; premature;
immature; <as>as, a <ex>timeless</ex> grave</as>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Must I behold thy <qex>timeless</qex>, cruel death?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Having no end; interminable; unending.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Timeless</xex> night and chaos.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Young.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Timelessly</ent>⟦br⟧
